com.versant.util
Interface CppListIterator

public interface CppListIterator

An Iterator for CppLists that allows you to traverse the CppList in either direction and modify the list during iteration.

Method Detail

hasNext

boolean hasNext()
Return the current status of the iterator.

This method returns true if this CppListIterator has more elements when traversing the list in the forward direction. (In other words, returns true if next() would return an element rather than throwing an exception.)

next

java.lang.Object next()
Returns the next element in the CppList. This method may be called repeatedly to iterate through the CppList, or intermixed with calls to previous to go back and forth. (Note that alternating calls to next and previous will return the same element repeatedly.)

Throws:
NoSuchElementException - iteration has no next element.

hasPrevious

boolean hasPrevious()
Returns true if this CppListIterator has more elements when traversing the list in the reverse direction. (In other words, returns true if previous would return an element rather than throwing an exception.)

previous

java.lang.Object previous()
Returns the previous element in the CppList. This method may be called repeatedly to iterate through the list backwards, or intermixed with calls to next to go back and forth. (Note that alternating calls to next and previous will return the same element repeatedly.)

Throws:
NoSuchElementException - iteration has no previous element.

nextIndex

int nextIndex()
Returns the index of the element that would be returned by a subsequent call to next. (Returns CppList size if the CppListIterator is at the end of the list.)

previousIndex

int previousIndex()
Returns the index of the element that would be returned by a subsequent call to previous. (Returns -1 if the CppListIterator is at the beginning of the list.)

remove

void remove()
Removes from the CppList the last element that was returned by next or previous. This call can only be made once per call to next or previous.

Throws:
NoSuchElementException - neither next nor previous have been called, or remove has already been called after the last call to next or previous.

set

void set(java.lang.Object o)
Replaces the last element returned by next or previous with the specified element.

Throws:
NoSuchElementException - neither next nor previous have been called, or remove was called after the last call to next or previous.

add

void add(java.lang.Object o)
Inserts the specified element into the CppList. The element is inserted immediately before the next element that would be returned by getNext, if any, and after the next element that would be returned by getPrevious, if any. (If the CppList contains no elements, the new element becomes the sole element on the CppList.) This call does not move the cursor: a subsequent call to next would return the element that was added by the call, and a subsequent call to previous would be unaffected.
